r2-12 What is the period of \(g(t)\)? \[g(t) \equiv \text{dnorm}\left(\frac{2\pi}{5}(t-3)\right)\] [rev-2]

[] 1 [] 5 [] \(2 \pi/5\) [] \(5/2\pi\) [a] \(g(t)\) isnt periodic. [The only one of our basic modeling functions that is period is \(\sin()\). The gaussian, that is, \(\text{dnorm}()\), has just one bump and therefore isnt periodic.]

r2-13 What is the period of \(g(t)\)? \[g(t) \equiv \frac{5}{\sin(2 \pi t)}\] [rev-2]
